windowStartTime.description: The start time of the backup window during which this the backup was attempted in [RFC 3339](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3339) format, for example `2012-11-15T16:19:00.094Z`.

startTime.description: The time the backup operation actually started in UTC timezone in [RFC 3339](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3339) format, for example `2012-11-15T16:19:00.094Z`.

backupKind.description: Specifies the kind of backup, PHYSICAL or DEFAULT_SNAPSHOT.
enumDescriptions: This is an unknown BackupKind.
The snapshot based backups
Physical backups
The status of the run is unknown.
The backup operation was enqueued.
The backup is overdue across a given backup window. Indicates a problem. Example: Long-running operation in progress during the whole window.
The backup is in progress.
The backup failed.
The backup was successful.
The backup was skipped (without problems) for a given backup window. Example: Instance was idle.
The backup is about to be deleted.
The backup deletion failed.
The backup has been deleted.

instance.description: Name of the database instance.

description.description: The description of this run, only applicable to on-demand backups.

timeZone.description: Backup time zone to prevent restores to an instance with a different time zone. Now relevant only for SQL Server.

diskEncryptionConfiguration.description: Encryption configuration specific to a backup.

endTime.description: The time the backup operation completed in UTC timezone in [RFC 3339](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3339) format, for example `2012-11-15T16:19:00.094Z`.

id.description: The identifier for this backup run. Unique only for a specific Cloud SQL instance.

scheduleDeadlineTime.description: Maintenance cannot be rescheduled to start beyond this deadline.

startTime.description: The start time of any upcoming scheduled maintenance for this instance.

canReschedule.description: If the scheduled maintenance can be rescheduled.

SqlScheduledMaintenance.description: Any scheduled maintenance for this instance.

enumDescriptions: This is an unknown flag type.

Integer type flag.
Flag type used for a server startup option.
Type introduced specially for MySQL TimeZone offset. Accept a string value with the format [-12:59, 13:00].

Comma-separated list of the strings in a SqlFlagType enum.
type.description: The type of the flag. Flags are typed to being `BOOLEAN`, `STRING`, `INTEGER` or `NONE`. `NONE` is used for flags which do not take a value, such as `skip_grant_tables`.

name.description: This is the name of the flag. Flag names always use underscores, not hyphens, for example: `max_allowed_packet`

minValue.description: For `INTEGER` flags, the minimum allowed value.

allowedIntValues.description: Use this field if only certain integers are accepted. Can be combined with min_value and max_value to add additional values.

appliesTo.description: The database version this flag applies to. Can be MySQL instances: `MYSQL_8_0`, `MYSQL_8_0_18`, `MYSQL_8_0_26`, `MYSQL_5_7`, or `MYSQL_5_6`. PostgreSQL instances: `POSTGRES_9_6`, `POSTGRES_10`, `POSTGRES_11` or `POSTGRES_12`. SQL Server instances: `SQLSERVER_2017_STANDARD`, `SQLSERVER_2017_ENTERPRISE`, `SQLSERVER_2017_EXPRESS`, `SQLSERVER_2017_WEB`, `SQLSERVER_2019_STANDARD`, `SQLSERVER_2019_ENTERPRISE`, `SQLSERVER_2019_EXPRESS`, or `SQLSERVER_2019_WEB`. See [the complete list](/sql/docs/mysql/admin-api/rest/v1/SqlDatabaseVersion).

requiresRestart.description: Indicates whether changing this flag will trigger a database restart. Only applicable to Second Generation instances.

maxValue.description: For `INTEGER` flags, the maximum allowed value.

inBeta.description: Whether or not the flag is considered in beta.

allowedStringValues.description: For `STRING` flags, a list of strings that the value can be set to.

binLogPosition.description: Position (offset) within the binary log file.

binLogFileName.description: Name of the binary log file for a Cloud SQL instance.
